    "caption": "The world's loudest eater, and extremely proud of it.",
    "shortDescription": "Tasmanian devils are the size of a small dog but have the most powerful bite relative to body size of any living mammal — they're such thorough eaters that they can finish an entire meal, leaving almost nothing behind. They get their name from the blood-curdling screeches, growls, and screams they make while competing over food, which can be heard from a kilometre away at night. Fun fact: Tasmanian devils glow blue-green under ultraviolet light — nobody is completely sure why."
